#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="dn11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "dn11:0.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 11 "
msgstr "Long Discourses 11 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn11:0.2"
msgid "Kevaṭṭasutta "
msgstr "With Kevaddha "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts-cs1, pts-vp-pli1.211, sc1
msgctxt "dn11:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "dn11:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā nāḷandāyaṃ viharati pāvārikambavane. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Nālandā in Pāvārika’s mango grove. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn11:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho kevaṭṭo gahapatiputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho kevaṭṭo gahapatiputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the householder Kevaddha went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him, "

msgctxt "dn11:1.4"
msgid "“ayaṃ, bhante, nāḷandā iddhā ceva phītā ca bahujanā ākiṇṇamanussā bhagavati abhippasannā. "
msgstr "“Sir, this Nāḷandā is successful and prosperous and full of people. "

msgctxt "dn11:1.5"
msgid "Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ samādisatu, yo uttari manussadhammā iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ karissati; "
msgstr "Sir, please direct a mendicant to perform a demonstration of superhuman psychic power. "

msgctxt "dn11:1.6"
msgid "evāyaṃ nāḷandā bhiyyoso mattāya bhagavati abhippasīdissatī”ti. "
msgstr "Then Nāḷandā will become even more devoted to the Buddha!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn11:1.7"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā kevaṭṭaṃ gahapatiputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, The Buddha said, "

msgctxt "dn11:1.8"
msgid "“na kho ahaṃ, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ desemi: "
msgstr "“Kevaddha, I do not teach the mendicants like this: "

msgctxt "dn11:1.9"
msgid "‘etha tumhe, bhikkhave, gihīnaṃ odātavasanānaṃ uttari manussadhammā iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ karothā’”ti. "
msgstr "‘Come now, mendicants, perform a demonstration of superhuman psychic power for the white-clothed laypeople.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2, pts-vp-pli1.212, sc2
msgctxt "dn11:2.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho kevaṭṭo gahapatiputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "For a second time, Kevaddha made the same request, "

msgctxt "dn11:2.2"
msgid "“nāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ dhaṃsemi; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:2.3"
msgid "api ca evaṃ vadāmi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:2.4"
msgid "‘ayaṃ, bhante, nāḷandā iddhā ceva phītā ca bahujanā ākiṇṇamanussā bhagavati abhippasannā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:2.5"
msgid "Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ samādisatu, yo uttari manussadhammā iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ karissati; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:2.6"
msgid "evāyaṃ nāḷandā bhiyyoso mattāya bhagavati abhippasīdissatī’”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:2.7"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho bhagavā kevaṭṭaṃ gahapatiputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and the Buddha gave the same answer. "

msgctxt "dn11:2.8"
msgid "“na kho ahaṃ, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ desemi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:2.9"
msgid "‘etha tumhe, bhikkhave, gihīnaṃ odātavasanānaṃ uttari manussadhammā iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ karothā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3, sc3
msgctxt "dn11:3.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho kevaṭṭo gahapatiputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "For a third time, Kevaddha made the same request, "

msgctxt "dn11:3.2"
msgid "“nāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ dhaṃsemi; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:3.3"
msgid "api ca evaṃ vadāmi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:3.4"
msgid "‘ayaṃ, bhante, nāḷandā iddhā ceva phītā ca bahujanā ākiṇṇamanussā bhagavati abhippasannā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:3.5"
msgid "Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ samādisatu, yo uttari manussadhammā iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ karissati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:3.6"
msgid "Evāyaṃ nāḷandā bhiyyoso mattāya bhagavati abhippasīdissatī’”ti. "
msgstr "and the Buddha said the following. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn11:3.7"
msgid "1. Iddhipāṭihāriya "
msgstr "1. The Demonstration of Psychic Power "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "dn11:3.8"
msgid "“Tīṇi kho imāni, kevaṭṭa, pāṭihāriyāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditāni. "
msgstr "“Kevaddha, there are three kinds of demonstration, which I declare having realized them with my own insight. "

msgctxt "dn11:3.9"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "dn11:3.10"
msgid "Iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ, ādesanāpāṭihāriyaṃ, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ. "
msgstr "The demonstration of psychic power, the demonstration of revealing, and the demonstration of instruction. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs4, sc5
msgctxt "dn11:4.1"
msgid "Katamañca, kevaṭṭa, iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is the demonstration of psychic power? "

msgctxt "dn11:4.2"
msgid "Idha, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti—ekopi hutvā bahudhā hoti, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hoti; āvibhāvaṃ tirobhāvaṃ tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ asajjamāno gacchati seyyathāpi ākāse; pathaviyāpi ummujjanimujjaṃ karoti seyyathāpi udake; udakepi abhijjamāne gacchati seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ; ākāsepi pallaṅkena kamati seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo; imepi candimasūriye evaṃ mahiddhike evaṃ mahānubhāve pāṇinā parāmasati parimajjati; yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti. "
msgstr "It’s a mendicant who wields the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying themselves and becoming one again; going unimpeded through a wall, a rampart, or a mountain as if through space; diving in and out of the earth as if it were water; walking on water as if it were earth; flying cross-legged through the sky like a bird; touching and stroking with the hand the sun and moon, so mighty and powerful; controlling the body as far as the Brahmā realm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.213, sc6
msgctxt "dn11:4.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aññataro saddho pasanno passati taṃ bhikkhuṃ anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhontaṃ—ekopi hutvā bahudhā hontaṃ, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hontaṃ; āvibhāvaṃ tirobhāvaṃ; tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ asajjamānaṃ gacchantaṃ seyyathāpi ākāse; pathaviyāpi ummujjanimujjaṃ karontaṃ seyyathāpi udake; udakepi abhijjamāne gacchantaṃ seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ; ākāsepi pallaṅkena kamantaṃ seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo; imepi candimasūriye evaṃ mahiddhike evaṃ mahānubhāve pāṇinā parāmasantaṃ parimajjantaṃ yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vattentaṃ. "
msgstr "Then someone with faith and confidence sees that mendicant performing those superhuman feats. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "dn11:4.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ so saddho pasanno aññatarassa assaddhassa appasannassa āroceti: "
msgstr "They tell someone else who lacks faith and confidence: "

msgctxt "dn11:4.5"
msgid "‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho, samaṇassa mahiddhikatā mahānubhāvatā. "
msgstr "‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing! The ascetic has such psychic power and might! "

msgctxt "dn11:4.6"
msgid "Amāhaṃ bhikkhuṃ addasaṃ anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhontaṃ—ekopi hutvā bahudhā hontaṃ, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hontaṃ … pe … yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vattentan’ti. "
msgstr "I saw him myself, performing all these superhuman feats!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs5, sc8
msgctxt "dn11:5.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ so assaddho appasanno taṃ saddhaṃ pasannaṃ evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "But the one lacking faith and confidence would say to them: "

msgctxt "dn11:5.2"
msgid "‘atthi kho, bho, gandhārī nāma vijjā. "
msgstr "‘There’s a spell named Gandhārī. "

msgctxt "dn11:5.3"
msgid "Tāya so bhikkhu anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti—ekopi hutvā bahudhā hoti, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hoti … pe … yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vattetī’ti. "
msgstr "Using that a mendicant can perform such superhuman feats.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "dn11:5.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, kevaṭṭa, "
msgstr "What do you think, Kevaddha? "

msgctxt "dn11:5.5"
msgid "api nu so assaddho appasanno taṃ saddhaṃ pasannaṃ evaṃ vadeyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Wouldn’t someone lacking faith speak like that?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn11:5.6"
msgid "“Vadeyya, bhante”ti. "
msgstr "“They would, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn11:5.7"
msgid "“Imaṃ kho ahaṃ, kevaṭṭa, iddhipāṭihāriye ādīnavaṃ sampassamāno iddhipāṭihāriyena aṭṭīyāmi harāyāmi jigucchāmi. "
msgstr "“Seeing this drawback in psychic power, I’m horrified, repelled, and disgusted by demonstrations of psychic power. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn11:5.8"
msgid "2. Ādesanāpāṭihāriya "
msgstr "2. The Demonstration of Revealing "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs6, sc10
msgctxt "dn11:6.1"
msgid "Katamañca, kevaṭṭa, ādesanāpāṭihāriyaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is the demonstration of revealing? "

msgctxt "dn11:6.2"
msgid "Idha, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cittampi ādisati, cetasikampi ādisati, vitakkitampi ādisati, vicāritampi ādisati: "
msgstr "In one case, someone reveals the mind, mentality, thoughts, and reflections of other beings and individuals: "

msgctxt "dn11:6.3"
msgid "‘evampi te mano, itthampi te mano, itipi te cittan’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is what you’re thinking, such is your thought, and thus is your state of mind.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.214, sc11
msgctxt "dn11:6.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aññataro saddho pasanno passati taṃ bhikkhuṃ parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cittampi ādisantaṃ, cetasikampi ādisantaṃ, vitakkitampi ādisantaṃ, vicāritampi ādisantaṃ: "
msgstr "Then someone with faith and confidence sees that mendicant revealing another person’s thoughts. "

msgctxt "dn11:6.5"
msgid "‘evampi te mano, itthampi te mano, itipi te cittan’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:6.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ so saddho pasanno aññatarassa assaddhassa appasannassa āroceti: "
msgstr "They tell someone else who lacks faith and confidence: "

msgctxt "dn11:6.7"
msgid "‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho, samaṇassa mahiddhikatā mahānubhāvatā. "
msgstr "‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing! The ascetic has such psychic power and might! "

msgctxt "dn11:6.8"
msgid "Amāhaṃ bhikkhuṃ addasaṃ parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cittampi ādisantaṃ, cetasikampi ādisantaṃ, vitakkitampi ādisantaṃ, vicāritampi ādisantaṃ: "
msgstr "I saw him myself, revealing the thoughts of another person!’ "

msgctxt "dn11:6.9"
msgid "“evampi te mano, itthampi te mano, itipi te cittan”’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs7, sc12
msgctxt "dn11:7.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ so assaddho appasanno taṃ saddhaṃ pasannaṃ evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "But the one lacking faith and confidence would say to them: "

msgctxt "dn11:7.2"
msgid "‘atthi kho, bho, maṇikā nāma vijjā; "
msgstr "‘There’s a spell named Māṇikā. "

msgctxt "dn11:7.3"
msgid "tāya so bhikkhu parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cittampi ādisati, cetasikampi ādisati, vitakkitampi ādisati, vicāritampi ādisati: "
msgstr "Using that a mendicant can reveal another person’s thoughts.’ "

msgctxt "dn11:7.4"
msgid "“evampi te mano, itthampi te mano, itipi te cittan”’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "dn11:7.5"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, kevaṭṭa, "
msgstr "What do you think, Kevaddha? "

msgctxt "dn11:7.6"
msgid "api nu so assaddho appasanno taṃ saddhaṃ pasannaṃ evaṃ vadeyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Wouldn’t someone lacking faith speak like that?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn11:7.7"
msgid "“Vadeyya, bhante”ti. "
msgstr "“They would, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn11:7.8"
msgid "“Imaṃ kho ahaṃ, kevaṭṭa, ādesanāpāṭihāriye ādīnavaṃ sampassamāno ādesanāpāṭihāriyena aṭṭīyāmi harāyāmi jigucchāmi. "
msgstr "“Seeing this drawback in psychic power, I’m horrified, repelled, and disgusted by demonstrations of psychic power. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn11:7.9"
msgid "3. Anusāsanīpāṭihāriya "
msgstr "3. The Demonstration of Instruction "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs8, sc14
msgctxt "dn11:8.1"
msgid "Katamañca, kevaṭṭa, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is the demonstration of instruction? "

msgctxt "dn11:8.2"
msgid "Idha, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu evamanusāsati: "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant instructs others like this: "

msgctxt "dn11:8.3"
msgid "‘evaṃ vitakketha, mā evaṃ vitakkayittha, evaṃ manasikarotha, mā evaṃ manasākattha, idaṃ pajahatha, idaṃ upasampajja viharathā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Think like this, not like that. Focus your mind like this, not like that. Give up this, and live having achieved that.’ "

msgctxt "dn11:8.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, kevaṭṭa, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ. "
msgstr "This is called the demonstration of instruction. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs9-66, pts-vp-pli1.215, sc15
msgctxt "dn11:9-66.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, kevaṭṭa, idha tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, a Realized One arises in the world … "

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.2"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti … pe … "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is accomplished in ethics. … "

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.3"
msgid "paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "They enter and remain in the first absorption … "

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.4"
msgid "Idampi vuccati, kevaṭṭa, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "This is called the demonstration of instruction. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn11:9-66.5"
msgid "dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "They enter and remain in the second absorption … "

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.6"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "third absorption … "

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.7"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "fourth absorption. "

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.8"
msgid "Idampi vuccati, kevaṭṭa, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "This too is called the demonstration of instruction. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn11:9-66.9"
msgid "ñāṇadassanāya cittaṃ abhinīharati abhininnāmeti … pe … "
msgstr "They extend and project the mind toward knowledge and vision … "

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.10"
msgid "idampi vuccati, kevaṭṭa, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "This too is called the demonstration of instruction. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn11:9-66.11"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti … pe … "
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’ "

msgctxt "dn11:9-66.12"
msgid "idampi vuccati, kevaṭṭa, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ. "
msgstr "This too is called the demonstration of instruction. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs67, sc16
msgctxt "dn11:67.1"
msgid "Imāni kho, kevaṭṭa, tīṇi pāṭihāriyāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditāni. "
msgstr "These, Kevaddha, are the three kinds of demonstration, which I declare having realized them with my own insight. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn11:67.2"
msgid "4. Bhūtanirodhesakabhikkhuvatthu "
msgstr "4. On the Mendicant In Search of the Cessation of Being "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "dn11:67.3"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, kevaṭṭa, imasmiññeva bhikkhusaṅghe aññatarassa bhikkhuno evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "Once it so happened, Kevaddha, that a mendicant in this very Saṅgha had the following thought, "

msgctxt "dn11:67.4"
msgid "‘kattha nu kho ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti? "
msgstr "‘Where do these four primary elements cease without anything left over, namely, the elements of earth, water, fire, and air?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs68, sc18
msgctxt "dn11:68.1"
msgid "Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu tathārūpaṃ samādhiṃ samāpajji, yathāsamāhite citte devayāniyo maggo pāturahosi. "
msgstr "Then that mendicant attained a state of immersion such that a path to the gods appeared. "

msgctxt "dn11:68.2"
msgid "Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu yena cātumahārājikā devā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā cātumahārājike deve etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then he approached the Gods of the Four Great Kings and said, "

msgctxt "dn11:68.3"
msgid "‘kattha nu kho, āvuso, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti? "
msgstr "‘Reverends, where do these four primary elements cease without anything left over, namely, the elements of earth, water, fire, and air?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.216, sc19
msgctxt "dn11:68.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kevaṭṭa, cātumahārājikā devā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "When he said this, those gods said to him, "

msgctxt "dn11:68.5"
msgid "‘mayampi kho, bhikkhu, na jānāma: "
msgstr "‘Mendicant, we too do not know this. "

msgctxt "dn11:68.6"
msgid "“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:68.7"
msgid "Atthi kho, bhikkhu, cattāro mahārājāno amhehi abhikkantatarā ca paṇītatarā ca. "
msgstr "But the Four Great Kings are our superiors. "

msgctxt "dn11:68.8"
msgid "Te kho etaṃ jāneyyuṃ: "
msgstr "They might know.’ "

msgctxt "dn11:68.9"
msgid "“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs69, sc20
msgctxt "dn11:69.1"
msgid "Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu yena cattāro mahārājāno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā cattāro mahārāje etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then he approached the Four Great Kings and asked the same question. "

msgctxt "dn11:69.2"
msgid "‘kattha nu kho, āvuso, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:69.3"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kevaṭṭa, cattāro mahārājāno taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "But they also said to him, "

msgctxt "dn11:69.4"
msgid "‘mayampi kho, bhikkhu, na jānāma: "
