msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kevaṭṭa, vasavattī devaputto taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:79.4"
msgid "‘ahampi kho, bhikkhu, na jānāmi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:79.5"
msgid "“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:79.6"
msgid "Atthi kho, bhikkhu, brahmakāyikā nāma devā amhehi abhikkantatarā ca paṇītatarā ca. "
msgstr "the gods of Brahmā’s Host. "

msgctxt "dn11:79.7"
msgid "Te kho etaṃ jāneyyuṃ: "
msgstr "They might know.’ "

msgctxt "dn11:79.8"
msgid "“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs80, sc24
msgctxt "dn11:80.1"
msgid "Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu tathārūpaṃ samādhiṃ samāpajji, yathāsamāhite citte brahmayāniyo maggo pāturahosi. "
msgstr "Then that mendicant attained a state of immersion such that a path to Brahmā appeared. "

msgctxt "dn11:80.2"
msgid "Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu yena brahmakāyikā devā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā brahmakāyike deve etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then he approached those gods and said, "

msgctxt "dn11:80.3"
msgid "‘kattha nu kho, āvuso, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti? "
msgstr "‘Reverends, where do these four primary elements cease without anything left over, namely, the elements of earth, water, fire, and air?’ "

msgctxt "dn11:80.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kevaṭṭa, brahmakāyikā devā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "But they also said to him, "

msgctxt "dn11:80.5"
msgid "‘mayampi kho, bhikkhu, na jānāma: "
msgstr "‘Mendicant, we too do not know this. "

msgctxt "dn11:80.6"
msgid "“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn11:80.7"
msgid "Atthi kho, bhikkhu, brahmā mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso vasavattī issaro kattā nimmātā seṭṭho sajitā vasī pitā bhūtabhabyānaṃ amhehi abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro ca. "
msgstr "But there is Brahmā, the Great Brahmā, the Undefeated, the Champion, the Universal Seer, the Wielder of Power, the Lord God, the Maker, the Author, the Best, the Begetter, the Controller, the Father of those who have been born and those yet to be born. He is our superior. "

msgctxt "dn11:80.8"
msgid "So kho etaṃ jāneyya: "
msgstr "He might know.’ "

msgctxt "dn11:80.9"
msgid "“yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.221, sc25
msgctxt "dn11:80.10"
msgid "‘Kahaṃ panāvuso, etarahi so mahābrahmā’ti? "
msgstr "‘But reverends, where is that Brahmā now?’ "

msgctxt "dn11:80.11"
msgid "‘Mayampi kho, bhikkhu, na jānāma, yattha vā brahmā yena vā brahmā yahiṃ vā brahmā; "
msgstr "‘We also don’t know where he is or what way he lies. "

msgctxt "dn11:80.12"
msgid "api ca, bhikkhu, yathā nimittā dissanti, āloko sañjāyati, obhāso pātubhavati, brahmā pātubhavissati, brahmuno hetaṃ pubbanimittaṃ pātubhāvāya, yadidaṃ āloko sañjāyati, obhāso pātubhavatī’ti. "
msgstr "But by the signs that are seen—light arising and radiance appearing—we know that Brahmā will appear. For this is the precursor for the appearance of Brahmā, namely light arising and radiance appearing.’ "

#. REF: pts-cs81
msgctxt "dn11:81.1"
msgid "Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, mahābrahmā nacirasseva pāturahosi. "
msgstr "Not long afterwards, the Great Brahmā appeared. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc26
msgctxt "dn11:81.2"
msgid "Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu yena so mahābrahmā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ mahābrahmānaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then that mendicant approached the Great Brahmā and said to him, "

msgctxt "dn11:81.3"
msgid "‘kattha nu kho, āvuso, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti? "
msgstr "‘Reverend, where do these four primary elements cease without anything left over, namely, the elements of earth, water, fire, and air?’ "

msgctxt "dn11:81.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kevaṭṭa, so mahābrahmā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Great Brahmā said to him, "

msgctxt "dn11:81.5"
msgid "‘ahamasmi, bhikkhu, brahmā mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso vasavattī issaro kattā nimmātā seṭṭho sajitā vasī pitā bhūtabhabyānan’ti. "
msgstr "‘I am Brahmā, the Great Brahmā, the Undefeated, the Champion, the Universal Seer, the Wielder of Power, the Lord God, the Maker, the Author, the Best, the Begetter, the Controller, the Father of those who have been born and those yet to be born.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs82, sc27
msgctxt "dn11:82.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu taṃ mahābrahmānaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "For a second time, that mendicant said to the Great Brahmā, "

msgctxt "dn11:82.2"
msgid "‘na khohaṃ taṃ, āvuso, evaṃ pucchāmi: "
msgstr "‘Reverend, I am not asking you whether you are "

msgctxt "dn11:82.3"
msgid "“tvamasi brahmā mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso vasavattī issaro kattā nimmātā seṭṭho sajitā vasī pitā bhūtabhabyānan”ti. "
msgstr "Brahmā, the Great Brahmā, the Undefeated, the Champion, the Universal Seer, the Wielder of Power, the Lord God, the Maker, the Author, the Best, the Begetter, the Controller, the Father of those who have been born and those yet to be born. "

msgctxt "dn11:82.4"
msgid "Evañca kho ahaṃ taṃ, āvuso, pucchāmi: "
msgstr "I am asking "

msgctxt "dn11:82.5"
msgid "“kattha nu kho, āvuso, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”’ti? "
msgstr "where these four primary elements cease without anything left over.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc28
msgctxt "dn11:82.6"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho so, kevaṭṭa, mahābrahmā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "For a second time, the Great Brahmā said to him, "

msgctxt "dn11:82.7"
msgid "‘ahamasmi, bhikkhu, brahmā mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso vasavattī issaro kattā nimmātā seṭṭho sajitā vasī pitā bhūtabhabyānan’ti. "
msgstr "‘I am Brahmā, the Great Brahmā, the Undefeated, the Champion, the Universal Seer, the Wielder of Power, the Lord God, the Maker, the Author, the Best, the Begetter, the Controller, the Father of those who have been born and those yet to be born.’ "

#. REF: pts-cs83
msgctxt "dn11:83.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu taṃ mahābrahmānaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "For a third time, that mendicant said to the Great Brahmā, "

msgctxt "dn11:83.2"
msgid "‘na khohaṃ taṃ, āvuso, evaṃ pucchāmi: "
msgstr "‘Reverend, I am not asking you whether you are "

msgctxt "dn11:83.3"
msgid "“tvamasi brahmā mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso vasavattī issaro kattā nimmātā seṭṭho sajitā vasī pitā bhūtabhabyānan”ti. "
msgstr "Brahmā, the Great Brahmā, the Undefeated, the Champion, the Universal Seer, the Wielder of Power, the Lord God, the Maker, the Author, the Best, the Begetter, the Controller, the Father of those who have been born and those yet to be born. "

msgctxt "dn11:83.4"
msgid "Evañca kho ahaṃ taṃ, āvuso, pucchāmi: "
msgstr "I am asking "

msgctxt "dn11:83.5"
msgid "“kattha nu kho, āvuso, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū”’ti? "
msgstr "where these four primary elements cease without anything left over.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.222, sc29
msgctxt "dn11:83.6"
msgid "Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, mahābrahmā taṃ bhikkhuṃ bāhāyaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ apanetvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the Great Brahmā took that mendicant by the arm, led him off to one side, and said to him, "

msgctxt "dn11:83.7"
msgid "‘ime kho maṃ, bhikkhu, brahmakāyikā devā evaṃ jānanti, “natthi kiñci brahmuno aññātaṃ, natthi kiñci brahmuno adiṭṭhaṃ, natthi kiñci brahmuno aviditaṃ, natthi kiñci brahmuno asacchikatan”ti. "
msgstr "‘Mendicant, these gods think that there is nothing at all that I don’t know and see and understand and realize. "

msgctxt "dn11:83.8"
msgid "Tasmāhaṃ tesaṃ sammukhā na byākāsiṃ. "
msgstr "That’s why I didn’t answer in front of them. "

msgctxt "dn11:83.9"
msgid "Ahampi kho, bhikkhu, na jānāmi yatthime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātūti. "
msgstr "But I too do not know where these four primary elements cease with nothing left over. "

msgctxt "dn11:83.10"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhu, tuyhevetaṃ dukkaṭaṃ, tuyhevetaṃ aparaddhaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ taṃ bhagavantaṃ atidhāvitvā bahiddhā pariyeṭṭhiṃ āpajjasi imassa pañhassa veyyākaraṇāya. "
msgstr "Therefore, mendicant, the misdeed is yours alone, the mistake is yours alone, in that you passed over the Buddha and searched elsewhere for an answer to this question. "

msgctxt "dn11:83.11"
msgid "Gaccha tvaṃ, bhikkhu, tameva bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamitvā imaṃ pañhaṃ puccha, yathā ca te bhagavā byākaroti, tathā naṃ dhāreyyāsī’ti. "
msgstr "Mendicant, go to the Buddha and ask him this question. You should remember it in line with his answer.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs84, sc30
msgctxt "dn11:84.1"
msgid "Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva brahmaloke antarahito mama purato pāturahosi. "
msgstr "Then that mendicant, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in front of me. "

msgctxt "dn11:84.2"
msgid "Atha kho so, kevaṭṭa, bhikkhu maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi, ekamantaṃ nisinno kho, kevaṭṭa, so bhikkhu maṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then he bowed, sat down to one side, and said to me, "

msgctxt "dn11:84.3"
msgid "‘kattha nu kho, bhante, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti? "
msgstr "‘Sir, where do these four primary elements cease without anything left over, namely, the elements of earth, water, fire, and air?’ "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn11:84.4"
msgid "4.1. Tīradassisakuṇupamā "
msgstr "4.1. The Simile of the Land-Spotting Bird "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs85, pts-vp-pli1.223, sc31
msgctxt "dn11:85.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, kevaṭṭa, taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocaṃ—"
msgstr "When he said this, I said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn11:85.2"
msgid "bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhu, sāmuddikā vāṇijā tīradassiṃ sakuṇaṃ gahetvā nāvāya samuddaṃ ajjhogāhanti. "
msgstr "‘Once upon a time, mendicant, some sea-merchants set sail for the ocean deeps, taking with them a land-spotting bird. "

msgctxt "dn11:85.3"
msgid "Te atīradakkhiniyā nāvāya tīradassiṃ sakuṇaṃ muñcanti. "
msgstr "When their ship was out of sight of land, they released the bird. "

msgctxt "dn11:85.4"
msgid "So gacchateva puratthimaṃ disaṃ, gacchati dakkhiṇaṃ disaṃ, gacchati pacchimaṃ disaṃ, gacchati uttaraṃ disaṃ, gacchati uddhaṃ disaṃ, gacchati anudisaṃ. "
msgstr "It flew right away to the east, the west, the north, the south, upwards, and in-between. "

#. VAR: tathāgatakova → tathā pakkantova (s1) | tathāpakkanto va (s2, s3)
msgctxt "dn11:85.5"
msgid "Sace so samantā tīraṃ passati, tathāgatakova hoti. "
msgstr "If it saw land on any side, it went there and stayed. "

msgctxt "dn11:85.6"
msgid "Sace pana so samantā tīraṃ na passati, tameva nāvaṃ paccāgacchati. "
msgstr "But if it saw no land on any side it returned to the ship. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn11:85.7"
msgid "Evameva kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, yato yāva brahmalokā pariyesamāno imassa pañhassa veyyākaraṇaṃ nājjhagā, atha mamaññeva santike paccāgato. "
msgstr "In the same way, after failing to get an answer to this question even after searching as far as the Brahmā realm, you’ve returned to me. "

msgctxt "dn11:85.8"
msgid "Na kho eso, bhikkhu, pañho evaṃ pucchitabbo: "
msgstr "Mendicant, this is not how the question should be asked: "

msgctxt "dn11:85.9"
msgid "‘kattha nu kho, bhante, ime cattāro mahābhūtā aparisesā nirujjhanti, seyyathidaṃ—pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, where do these four primary elements cease without anything left over, namely, the elements of earth, water, fire, and air?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc32
msgctxt "dn11:85.10"
msgid "Evañca kho eso, bhikkhu, pañho pucchitabbo: "
msgstr "This is how the question should be asked: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc33
msgctxt "dn11:85.11"
msgid "‘Kattha āpo ca pathavī, "
msgstr "“Where do water and earth, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.12"
msgid "tejo vāyo na gādhati; "
msgstr "fire and air find no footing; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.13"
msgid "Kattha dīghañca rassañca, "
msgstr "where do long and short, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.14"
msgid "aṇuṃ thūlaṃ subhāsubhaṃ; "
msgstr "fine and coarse, beautiful and ugly; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.15"
msgid "Kattha nāmañca rūpañca, "
msgstr "where do name and form "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.16"
msgid "asesaṃ uparujjhatī’ti. "
msgstr "cease with nothing left over?” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc34
msgctxt "dn11:85.17"
msgid "Tatra veyyākaraṇaṃ bhavati: "
msgstr "And the answer to that is: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc35
msgctxt "dn11:85.18"
msgid "‘Viññāṇaṃ anidassanaṃ, "
msgstr "“Consciousness that’s invisible, "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/whose-consciousness-is-invisible-infinite-and-all-radiant/4098
#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: sabbatopabhaṃ → \
msgctxt "dn11:85.19"
msgid "anantaṃ sabbatopabhaṃ; "
msgstr "infinite, radiant all round. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.20"
msgid "Ettha āpo ca pathavī, "
msgstr "Here’s where water and earth, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.21"
msgid "tejo vāyo na gādhati. "
msgstr "fire and air find no footing; "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc36
msgctxt "dn11:85.22"
msgid "Ettha dīghañca rassañca, "
msgstr "here’s where long and short, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.23"
msgid "aṇuṃ thūlaṃ subhāsubhaṃ; "
msgstr "fine and coarse, beautiful and ugly; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.24"
msgid "Ettha nāmañca rūpañca, "
msgstr "here’s where name and form "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.25"
msgid "asesaṃ uparujjhati; "
msgstr "cease with nothing left over—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.26"
msgid "Viññāṇassa nirodhena, "
msgstr "with the cessation of consciousness, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn11:85.27"
msgid "etthetaṃ uparujjhatī’”ti. "
msgstr "that’s where this ceases.”’” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc37
msgctxt "dn11:85.28"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
